1. Cut the pineapple lengthways into eighths. Leave the skin on.
2. Grill on the BBQ for a few minutes on each cut side of the fruit until you see nice caramelised grill marks.
3. After cooking run a knife between the skin and flesh and cut into segments – but serve intact on the skin.
4. Serve each quarter with a small bowl of reduced fat Greek yoghurt topped with the chopped macadamias.
